# Shadcn-First UI Policy

When building or updating UI in this repository, `shadcn` is the first choice.

- Start with existing components in `app/components/ui` before creating new primitives.
- Prefer composing screens from `shadcn` primitives instead of custom base components.
- If a needed primitive does not exist, add it in a `shadcn`-compatible structure and API style.
- Keep visual states in `class-variance-authority` patterns when variants are required.
- Preserve token-based Tailwind usage and avoid hardcoded color values.

Decision order:

1. Reuse an existing `app/components/ui` component.
2. Add/adapt a `shadcn`-style primitive.
3. Build custom UI only if options 1 and 2 are not viable.
